comments: Trent Jr. (TOR) extends his hands into Burks' (NYK) front and delivers contact that dislodges Burks from his position.
Trent Jr. (TOR) briefly has his arms around Randle's (NYK) upper half before correcting.
VanVleet (TOR) places his hand to Rose's (NYK) front and releases away as he dribbles toward the pick.
Siakam (TOR) firms up on his right foot and absorbs the contact with Rose (NYK) as he sets the pick.
Fournier (NYK) brings his right hand and left forearm toward Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs to Trent Jr.'s front as he starts his drive.
Fournier (NYK) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr. (TOR) during the follow-through.
Rose (NYK) moves toward Siakam (TOR) as he boxes out and marginal body contact occurs as Siakam elevates to back-tap the ball.
Barnes (TOR) and Burks (NYK) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Fournier (NYK) brushes Barnes' (TOR) right arm as Barnes is passing and marginal contact occurs.
Rose (NYK) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr.'s (TOR) left arm after the release.
Randle (NYK) firms up in his screening position in Barnes' (TOR) path and absorbs the contact.
Randle (NYK) engages and disengages with Barnes (TOR) along the lane line.
Siakam (TOR) maintains a rested forearm on Rose's (NYK) front as Rose drives into the lane and marginal contact occurs.
Champagnie (TOR) jumps toward Rose (NYK) and marginal body contact occurs as Rose is passing.
Barrett (NYK) brings his off-arm toward Trent Jr.'s (TOR) front and, as Barrett slows his momentum in the lane, marginal contact occurs when he releases away.
Barnes (TOR) makes marginal body contact with Barrett (NYK) as he contests the driving shot attempt.
Burks (NYK), Randle (NYK), and VanVleet (TOR) each elevate in pursuit of the rebound and incidental body/arm contact occurs after Burks deflects the ball.
Barrett (NYK) firms up in his screening position in Barnes' (TOR) path and absorbs the contact.
Randle (NYK) extends and delivers contact to Barnes' (TOR) side as he sets the screen, dislodging Barnes and affecting his ability to defend.
Replay review of the out of bounds call pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. VanVleet (TOR) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds. The game clock was reset to 0:51.2.
VanVleet (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Randle (NYK) before any incidental contact occurs.
Siakam's (TOR) right foot is out of bounds as he makes contact with the ball.
Siakam (TOR) and Randle (NYK) each make clean contact with the ball in the lane and the ball becomes dislodged as incidental contact occurs.
Siakam (TOR) and Randle (NYK) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
VanVleet (TOR) is out of bounds when he catches the ball.
Siakam (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball as Randle (NYK) starts his dribble.
VanVleet (TOR) raises his arm up and marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) left arm as Randle is passing.
Barnes (TOR) moves underneath Burks (NYK) and initiates contact with Burks' lower half that affects his shot attempt.
Rose (NYK) and VanVleet (TOR) engage and disengage with one another as VanVleet moves to set the pick.
Champagnie (TOR) brushes Randle's (NYK) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Randle retrieves the rebound.
Barnes (TOR) turns alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Barrett's drive.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Burks (NYK) commits a take foul on Trent Jr. (TOR).
Siakam (TOR) and Barnes (TOR) legally contest Barrett's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Barrett's left leg extends forward following the release to initiate the marginal contact with Barnes.
